steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"d10ef","text":"Prepare and collect all supplies necessary for the number of samples that will be concentrated using membrane filtration.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9kdkh","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"bqpoh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"b61fm","text":"All glassware, membrane filtration cups, and centrifuge bottles should be autoclaved with aluminum foil covering any opening","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8tgju","text":"Place all autoclaved and sterilized materials underneath the sterilized biological hood","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"f0j6i","text":"Place a biohazard benchtop waste bag into the biological hood on a stand for easy disposal of any contaminated material used during the procedure","type":"unordered-list-item"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7u6bo","text":"Remove the grab sample from the 4°C refrigerator and place under the sterilized biological hood.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c1n46","text":"Aseptically pour   of the grab sample into an autoclaved 500mL beaker that is labeled with a sample identifier using labeling tape.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":17,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"cqfjn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"300","error":false,"guid":"CDCF891059D111ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":2}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"27is5","text":"After 300mL of the grab sample has been measured, aseptically pour the aliquoted sample into an autoclaved centrifuge bottle that is labeled with the sample identifier using labeling tape.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fbot2","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"d6k2e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"aiscs","text":"Using sterilized forceps, ensure that the O-ring of the autoclaved centrifuge bottle is securely inside of the centrifuge bottle lid.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9bkbt","text":"Using aseptic technique, secure the centrifuged bottle lid onto the centrifuge bottle containing the sample and secure the lid by turning a quarter of the way past tight.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b8qkn","text":"Balance the sample centrifuge bottles using a benchtop scale that has been sterilized using 10% bleach solution followed by 70% ethanol solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3pg4g","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"82hg5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"2d4je","text":"The benchtop scale should be placed within the biological hood to ensure no sample contamination outside of the biological hood area.","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"6ka6j","text":"Measure each sample and centrifuge bottle with the lid attached and record the weight.","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"akprf","text":"Using DI water, adjust the weight of each sample centrifuge bottle to be within 0.5 grams of each other.","type":"unordered-list-item"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7uaee","text":"Centrifuge the sample(s) for   .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":29,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"rfgq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"duu39","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"d8alp","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9iegf","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":2,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"89mak","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"centrifuge","mutability":"","data":{"centrifuge":"5000","duration":300,"error_centrifuge":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"479787C059D211ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"scientificNotation":{"centrifuge":false,"temperature":false},"start":null,"temperature":"","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":33}},"1":{"type":"equipment","mutability":"","data":{"id":2963,"brand":"Thermo Scientific™","can_edit":0,"guid":"2B6B5A3059D311ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","link":"https://www.fishersci.no/shop/products/sorvall-rc-6-plus-centrifuge/12121680","name":"Sorvall™ RC 6 Plus","sku":"12121680","specifications":null,"type":"Centrifuge","vendor":{"id":31,"name":"Fisher Scientific","link":"https://www.fishersci.com/us/en/home.html","image":{"source":"/img/vendors/placeholder.png","placeholder":"/img/vendors/placeholder.png"}},"file":null,"image":null}},"2":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ev07s","text":"Ensure that the centrifuge is balanced and running properly according to manufacturer specifications.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"tmgv","text":"Remove the centrifuged sample(s) from the centrifuge and carefully place them back under the biological hood.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1na99","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fmt64","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8cjfh","text":"Take care to not disturb any pellet that has formed at the bottom of the centrifuge bottle.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bdcnn","text":"Use a Eppendorf Research Plus Single Channel Pipette to add   of BRSV aliquot into the sample.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":60,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2ttam","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fv05o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9udte","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"10","error":false,"guid":"DDC894F059DC11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"apif3","text":"Gently pipette to the second stop to expel all 10µL of BRSV into the sample.","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"9vfkk","text":"Use a new pipette tip for each sample.","type":"unordered-list-item"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"56urp","text":"Measure out   of MgCl2 using benchtop scale paper and an autoclaved chemical spatula.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":21,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":12,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"6tni","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"0.71","error":false,"guid":"E8B6B28059DB11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"+/- 0.02g","scientificNotation":false,"unit":6}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"carvo","text":"Pour the measured MgCl2 into the 500mL beaker that was initially used to measure the sample volume. Put a magnetic stir bar into the beaker and stir the sample on the stirrer for  .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":22,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":179,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"etvl7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":900,"guid":"B14DDDA0766811EDBB7D6F33ABAD781D","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2g68u","text":"Aseptically pour the centrifuged sample into the identically labeled 500mL beaker that now has the MgCl2 to create a final concentration of 25mM.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":103,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2j6vj","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"pi2h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8qpf8","text":"Ensure while pouring liquid samples to not pour any pellet or solids into the beaker along with the liquid.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dnq0i","text":"Place a benchtop calibrated pH probe underneath the biological hood and sterilize the probe, excluding the glass measurement part, and workspace with 10% bleach solution followed by 70% ethanol solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ehq2","text":"Adjust the pH to   +/- 0.1 using 5% HCl and 5% NaOH solutions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":17,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"btqo9","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1vegj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1l10u","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"ph","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"9782C65059DC11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"number":"3.5"}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8heg2","text":"Use individual pipette droppers for both the 5% HCl and 5% NaOH solutions (do not mix the pipettes).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"91cvd","text":"Cover the opening of the sample beakers with aluminum foil and secure the foil by either wrapping around the edge of the opening or with autoclave tape.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"95hlu","text":"Gently and carefully swirl the sample to allow for homogeneous mixing of the BRSV throughout the sample beaker.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4mqgl","text":"Place the sample beaker into a    refrigerator for  . ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":31,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":51,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"erpmn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"710A7D0059DD11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10}},"1":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":1800,"guid":"77CDC02059DD11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"914et","text":"While the sample sits in the refrigerator for 30 minutes, place an autoclaved membrane filtration cup into each of the vacuum manifold openings and secure with a quarter turn to create a seal.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6mli2","text":"Without disturbing the lower half portion of the membrane filtration cup, remove the top cup portion and place topside down onto the benchtop paper that was placed at the start of the procedure preparation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"384vb","text":"Using the sterilized forceps, aseptically place a 0.45µM membrane filter paper onto the opening of the membrane filtration cup that is still attached to the vacuum manifold.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1lhb2","text":"When initially setting up the vacuum membrane filtration manifold with filter papers, sterilization of forceps can be done a singular time when all membrane filter cups are autoclaved and placed into the biological hood on the vacuum manifold with no sample(s) present.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ijb3","text":"After all membrane filtration cups have a 0.45µM membrane filter paper placed onto their respective opening, reattach the top of the membrane filtration cups to their base.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"n7ur","text":"Re-sterilize the forceps and place into an aseptic position for later use after sample processing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"l4p7","text":"After the 30-minute refrigeration period is over, pour   of the sample into a membrane filtration cup that has the membrane filter paper and is sealed tightly on the vacuum manifold.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":55,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fo436","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9jut6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fofdq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"150","error":false,"guid":"B218974059ED11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":2}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"length":1,"offset":68}],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4rnl","text":"Place the remaining 150mL of sample within its beaker back into the   refrigerator while the sample is being processed through the vacuum manifold.","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"2u3mg","text":"","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{"0":{"data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"8A14A4E059EE11ECB571F5D1E678F6BB","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10},"mutability":"MUTABLE","type":"temperature"}}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4epsl","text":"Label the membrane filtration cups with their respective sample identifier.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aovo","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2l7sh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4ulaf","text":"Label on the individual membrane filtration cup using labeling tape or label the benchtop paper that is directly in front of the membrane filtration cup.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9c30i","text":"Check the seals of the vacuum hoses and vacuum flask to make sure that the seals are secure to prevent leakage of any sample liquid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e717n","text":"Turn the vacuum vent that is attached to the biological hood on to begin the vacuum process, and subsequently turn the valve on the vacuum manifold for each sample that is being processed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eivub","text":"Check the seal on the vacuum hoses and flask once again after the vacuum process has begun.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"81ch5","text":"Throughout the filtration process, frequently check the flow of sample liquid in the membrane filtration cups until the whole sample volume has filtered through the membrane. After 30-45 minutes, if the sample is draining very slowly and a large amount of sample volume still remains to be filtered, follow sub-steps 39.1 - 39.12.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":175,"length":155}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3h5ij","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8vhem","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4h405","text":"The margin of error of sample volume should be no more than 10% (15mL).","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"23ivf","text":"Sample turbidity can affect the speed of flow through and can also cause filter paper to clog, which inhibits the flow rate tremendously.","type":"unordered-list-item"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"72c61","text":"Retrieve the sample beaker from the 4°C and place under the biological hood.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cmp11","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"196n1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4l4p3","text":"Close the cap of the 1.7 mL tube containing the final RNA (you will have a final volume of  ).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":91,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"","data":{"amount":"100","error":false,"guid":"A66273AD73F611EC81520A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"r24h","text":"Turn on the biological hood vent and wait for airflow to start circulating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"si1o","text":"Carefully remove the vacuum flask and hoses that are attached to the vacuum vent within the biological hood and dispose of any liquid present in the correct biological hazard trash container.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"esmkg","text":"Wash and rinse the vacuum hoses using a mixture of hot water and concentrated bleach at a 2:1 ratio.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"al8k7","text":"Pour concentrated bleach solution into the vacuum flask to cover the entire bottom surface.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2h4s9","text":"Spray 10% bleach solution inside the biological hood and wipe all surfaces with paper towels.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7a3k4","text":"After spraying the 10% bleach solution, spray 70% ethanol solution inside the biological hood and wipe all surfaces with paper towels.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7fnb7","text":"Carefully reattach the vacuum flask and vacuum hoses to the vacuum vent within the biological hood.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6hg6","text":"Place two pieces of benchtop surface paper underneath the membrane filtration vacuum apparatus that is inside of the sterilized biological hood.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"etnh0","text":"Pour 100% ethanol into a smaller autoclaved beaker to a level that allows for the entire end of forceps to be submerged.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7n7rg","text":"Carefully light a alcohol lamp burner.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"77rbn","text":"Place the forceps that have been submerged in the 100% ethanol and burn the ethanol off to create a visible flame.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dr5nk","text":"Place the now sterilized forceps into the biological hood in a position so that the sterilized end is not touching a physical surface to remain aseptic.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bn1t3","text":"When forceps are used or come into contact with any surface or filter paper that is contaminated with a sample, they must be re-sterilized using the method given above.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
